the deception. The blood might almo&s;t
be &s;een to circulate in her veins, &s;o plainly did
they appear; and her eyes had the dazzling ra|diance
of ethereal fire, to which the hectic heat
of her glowing, though wafted countenance,
<PB N="306" REF="308">
&s;till added.&mdash;A few locks of her fine light
