<P><PB N="307" REF="309">
"I forgive him mo&s;t willingly," cried Ce|le&s;tina&mdash;"and
mo&s;t &s;incerely wi&s;h him
happy."</P>
<P>"Ah, Madam!" &s;aid Emily&mdash;"You mu&s;t
then carry your genero&s;ity farther&mdash;for you
only can make him &s;o&mdash;I dared to repre&s;ent
this in a letter to you&mdash;I now repeat it&mdash;vic|tim,
as I am, even in the morning of my days,
I &s;hould, however, die in peace, for I hope
my peace is made with Heaven&mdash;if I could
&s;ee any pro&s;pect of Vava&s;our's being happy;
reclaimed from that wild career where he is
now wa&s;ting his time, his fortune, and his
