<P>The &s;hort ceremony of reading the will be|ing
over, another was to be gone through
le&s;s ea&s;y to Mi&s;s Fitz-Hayman; which was,
announcing to her mother her actual marriage
with Captain Cavanaugh&mdash;which &s;he thought
<PB N="315" REF="317">
mu&s;t otherwi&s;e be revealed by &s;omebody
el&s;e.</P>
<P>The dialogue was &s;hort, but deci&s;ive&mdash;Mi&s;s
Fitz-Hayman, or rather Mrs. Cavanaugh,
had more courage than tenderne&s;s; and hav|ing
now nothing to fear from her mother's
