having mentioned his marriage, or his daugh|ter.&mdash;"Perhaps,
however," &s;aid &s;he, "he
might have rea&s;ons for this, which I cannot
<PB N="337" REF="339">
penetrate. My father was har&s;h, ob&s;tinate,
and avaricious; and always expected Ormond
