Thorold, and related to him all &s;he had learned
from Cele&s;tina the evening before.</P>
<P>"I now blame my&s;elf, my good friend,"
&s;aid &s;he, "for the part I have taken&mdash;but who
could fore&s;ee this?&mdash;Yet, I own, I fear the
con&s;equences, and heartily wi&s;h I had never
